olive oil
½ lemon
1 carrot
1 cucumber
½ packet firm tofu
1 packet ponzu sauce
1 tsp sesame oil
1 packet Shredded Cabbage Mix
1 packet Baby Leaves
1 sachet Sweet Soy Seasoning
1 packet sesame dressing
1 packet coriander
1 packet diced bacon

• Slice lemon into wedges. Using a vegetable peeler, peel carrot into ribbons. Thinly slice radish.
• Cut firm tofu (see ingredients) into 1cm chunks.
• In a medium bowl, combine sweet soy seasoning, the plain flour and a pinch of salt. Add tofu and toss to combine.

• In a large bowl, combine ponzu sauce, the sesame oil and a generous squeeze of lemon juice. Add carrot and toss to combine.
• Add radish, shredded cabbage mix and baby leaves to the carrot and toss to combine. Season to taste.

• In a large frying pan, heat a generous drizzle of olive oil over medium-high heat.
• When the oil is hot, cook tofu and diced bacon, breaking up with a spoon, until golden, 5-7 minutes.

• Divide ponzu carrot ribbon salad between bowls.
• Top with sweet soy tofu and diced bacon.
• Drizzle with sesame dressing. Tear over coriander to serve. Serve with any remaining lemon wedges. Enjoy!